I had been suffering from 2 trigger thumbs during the lockdown and could not get an appointment to see an orthopaedic, thankfully just after the final lockdown was over I searched the internet and found that Dr Khan was available.  Very few doctors were available at that time.  Dr Khan immediately saw the problem and explained in detail, the problem I had and suggest a small surgery on one of my hands.  It went very well.  He explained every step that was taken, as I had local anaesthetic and put me at ease.  It's been 10 days since the operation and I had movement back in my thumb almost immediately and the pain was gone.  Still need to take the stitches out, but very pleased with the whole experience.
